This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama in July 2015. It honors the victims of a tragedy in Chattanooga, Tennessee, where service members were killed. The proclamation expresses condolences and gratitude to the police officers and first responders who stopped the rampage and saved lives. It emphasizes that the American community will not give in to fear and cannot be divided. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims until July 25, 2015.